|section='''Encyclopædia''' <!-- article name -->
|sectionurl=https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/The_Encyclopedia_Americana_(1920)/Encyclop%C3%A6dia
|text=The first '''encyclopædia''' written in English and with the articles alphabetically arranged was the [[w:Lexicon Technicum|‘Lexicon Technicum,’]] {{...}} [in 1704], by [[w:John Harris (writer)|John Harris]], a London clergyman. This was a useful and popular work, though it omitted from its scope theology, biography, antiquity and poetry.}}
