===Pronunciation===
* {{sense|letter name}} {{IPA|id|/a/}}
* {{sense|phoneme}} {{IPA|id|/a/}}
* {{homophones|id|a|à}}

===Etymology 1===
From the {{der|id|la|-}} letter {{m|la|A}}, from the {{der|id|ett|-}} letter {{m|ett|𐌀}}, from the {{der|id|grc|-}} letter {{m|grc|Α||alpha}}, derived from the {{der|id|phn|-}} letter {{m|phn|𐤀||[[aleph]]}}, from the {{der|id|egy|-}} hieroglyph {{m|egy|𓃾}}.

====Letter====
{{letter|id}}

# {{Latn-def|id|letter|1}}

====See also====
* {{see-temp|list:Latin script letters/id}}

===Etymology 2===
From the initial position of the letter {{m|id|A}} in the Indonesian alphabet.

====Symbol====
{{head|id|symbol}}

# {{l|en|A}}:
## {{senseid|id|rank}} a rank, normally the highest rank, on any of various scales that assign letters
## {{senseid|id|grade}} {{lb|id|education}} the highest [[letter grade]] assigned (disregarding plusses and minuses)
## {{lb|id|music}} a tone three fifths above C in the [[cycle of fifths]]; the sixth tone of the C major scale; the first note of the minor scale of A minor; the reference tone that occurs at exactly 440 Hz; the printed or written note A; the [[scale]] with A as its [[keynote]]
# {{lb|id|vehicle-distinguishing signs}} vehicle number plate code for the Banten, Cilegon, Serang, Pandeglang, Lebak and Tangerang areas

===Etymology 3===
{{sense|blood type}} From {{m|en|w:ABO blood group system|A antigen}}

