===Etymology 2===
From {{inh|sco|enm|a}}, an unstressed form of {{m|enm|I}}, itself a reduced form of {{m|enm|ik}}, {{m|enm|ic}}, from {{inh|sco|ang|ic}}, from {{inh|sco|gmw-pro|*ik}}, from {{inh|sco|gem-pro|*ek||pos=pronoun|I}}, from {{inh|sco|ine-pro|*eǵh₂óm}}.

====Alternative forms====
* {{alter|sco|A'|Aa|Ah|Aw}}

====Pronunciation====
* {{IPA|sco|/ɑː/|/ɑɪ/|a=stressed}}
** {{IPA|sco|/ɛː/|a=Dundee}} {{q|sometimes spelled {{m|sco|Eh}}}}
* {{IPA|sco|/ə/|a=unstressed}}

====Pronoun====
{{head|sco|pronoun|cat2=personal pronouns}}

# [[I]] {{gloss|first-person singular pronoun}}
#* {{quote-book|sco|year=1901|author=Robert De Bruce Trotter|title=Galloway Gossip Eighty Years Ago: Being a Series of Articles Illustrative of the Manners, Customs, and Peculiarities of the Aboriginal Picts of Galloway|page=196
|text="'''A''' dinna think we could spare't fae the swine, puir things." "Wull ye tak a half-croon for yer pennyworth o' milk, than?" quo Wullie. "Weel! '''A''' dinna ken! A'm no sure if '''A''' durst; it wud scrimp the swine, puir things."}}

