===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|en|enm|raven}}, {{m|enm|reven|t=raven (''Corvus corax''); carrion crow (''Corvus corone''); rook (''Corvus frugilegus'') (?); the constellation Corvus; gall nuts of the Aleppo oak (''Quercus infectoria'') used to make black ink}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=rāven|pos=n|id=MED36027}}</ref> from {{inh|en|ang|hræfn|t=raven}},<ref>{{R:Anglo-Saxon Dictionary|page=551|column=2}}</ref> from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*hrabn|t=raven}}, from  {{inh|en|gem-pro|*hrabnaz|t=raven}}, probably from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ḱrep-|t=to crackle; to rattle}} or {{m|ine-pro|*ḱer-|t=to croak, crow}}, probably ultimately {{lg|onomatopoeic}}, referring to the bird’s call.<ref>{{R:OED Online|pos=n.''{{sup|1}} and ''adj|id=2302922263|date=December 2025|nodot=1}}; {{R:Lexico|pos=n}}</ref>

