===Adjective===
{{en-adj|er,more}}

# Having a brown [[colour]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Ashley Strickland|title=An unusual object is moving so fast it could escape the Milky Way. Scientists aren’t certain what it is|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2024/08/21/science/hypervelocity-star-escape-milky-way|date=2024-08-21|passage=But none of those '''brown''' dwarfs were speeding along on a trajectory that would carry them out of the galaxy like “runaway” hypervelocity stars observed by astronomers in the last two decades.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} {{U|gloomy}}.
# {{lb|en|sometimes [[capitalized]]}} Of or relating to any of various [[ethnic group]]s having dark [[pigmentation]] of the [[skin]].
## {{lb|en|US}} [[Latino]]/[[Latin American]]
##* {{quote-journal
|en|date=2015-11-02
|origyear=2014
|author=Susan Svrluga
|quotee=Ivonne Gonzalez
|title=Students accuse Yale SAE fraternity brother of saying ‘white girls only’ at party door
|journal=w:The Washington Post
|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151103102643/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/grade-point/wp/2015/11/02/students-accuse-yale-sae-fraternity-brothers-of-having-a-white-girls-only-policy-at-their-party/
|archivedate=03 November 2015
|issn=0190-8286
|oclc=2269358
|section=Grade Point
|url2=https://archive.is/Lt99U
|text=Reminds me of the time they asked me and a group of other Latino, predominantly Mexican, friends for our passports when we tried to go to their [expletive] party a little over a year ago.{{...}}<br>The saddest part is that I don’t think they understand why it’s insulting to ask a '''brown''' person for a passport.}}
## {{lb|en|US|broad|vague}} [[of color#Adjective|of color]].
## {{lb|en|of Asians and Africans}} [[South Asian]] or sometimes [[Middle Eastern]] or [[North African]]
##* {{quote-journal
|en|date=September 9, 2021
|quotee=w:Aasif Mandvi
|title=Transcript: Race in America: Giving Voice with Aasif Mandvi
|journal=w:The Washington Post
|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20230325221506/https://www.washingtonpost.com/washington-post-live/2021/09/09/transcript-race-america-giving-voice-with-aasif-mandvi/
|archivedate=25 March 2023
|issn=0190-8286
|oclc=2269358
|url2=https://archive.is/D30T7
|text=I think they sort of realized like, oh, we have Aasif who is a Muslim, an American, '''brown''' person, you know, who can sit on that fence between cultures and sort of talk about what it is--what this is from the perspective of being an insider and an outsider at the same time.{{...}}<br>I think there is in the sort of South Asian, you know, psyche, a kind of adoration of Western ideals and culture that was sort of implanted into us by the British, you know, and this idea that everything that is Western is superior and better than what we have and what India--you know, what is true to our own culture.}}
## {{lb|en|of East-Eurasian ancestry}} [[Southeast Asian]], [[Pacific Islander]], or sometimes [[Native American]]
##* {{quote-journal
|en|date=September 25, 2020
|author=Eric J. Daza
|title=How A 'Secret Asian Man' Embraced Anti-Racism
|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20210423163319/https://laist.com/news/race-in-la-how-a-secret-asian-man-embraced-anti-racism
|archivedate=23 April 2021
|work=w:LAist
|section=Essays
|url2=https://archive.is/UN71p
|text=I came to deeply embrace anti-racism in slow, sustained increments.<br>To do so, I had to embrace my own identity as a '''Brown''' person -- and understand my own complicity in white supremacy.{{...}}<br>I had grown up in an entire Southeast Asian culture that had largely been groomed, indoctrinated and brainwashed into white-centered thinking over some 450 years of colonization by our Western overlords: Spain for almost 400 years, and then the United States of America for nearly 50 years more.}}
# {{senseid|en|nongreen or antigreen}} Not [[green#English:_environmentally friendly|green]] ([[environment]]ally [[irresponsible]]); anti-[[green#English:_of a green party, environmentalism-oriented|green]] (against environmental protection).
#: {{nearsyn|en|nongreen|antigreen}}
#* {{quote-book |en |year=2011 |last=Wooldridge |first=Adrian |authorlink=Adrian Wooldridge |title=Masters of Management: How the Business Gurus and Their Ideas Have Changed the World — for Better and for Worse |publisher=HarperCollins Business |page=48 |passage=Tesco and Sainsbury, two of Britain’s biggest retailers, are locked in a fierce battle to prove who is greener. Even BSkyB, the British satellite outpost of the distinctly '''brown''' Murdoch empire, has declared itself “carbon-neutral.”}}

