===Etymology===
{{etymon|la|decem<id:ten>|id=twelfth month}}
By [[haplology]] from earlier {{m|la|*decumo-mēmbris}}, analogically to {{m|la|septem}} : {{m|la|September}}, from earlier {{m|la|*decumo-mēnsris}} "of the tenth month", from the ordinal stem {{m|la|decem||ten}} + *mēnsris, from {{m|la|mensis|mens-|month}} + {{m|la|-ris}}. In the [[w:Roman calendar|Roman calendar]], the year began with {{m|la|Mārtius||March}}, and ''December'' was the tenth month of the year.

