===Etymology===
{{etymon|en|:inh|enm:Januarie<ety:from<Janevere<ety:bor<xno:genever<ety:der<la:Iānuārius>>>>>>|tree=1}}
From {{inh|en|enm|Januarie}}, {{m|enm|januari}}, re-latinised forms of {{cog|enm|Janevere}}, {{m|enm|Ieneuer}}, from {{der|en|xno|genever}}, from {{der|en|la|Iānuārius||(month) of Janus}}, a compound of {{com|la|Iānus|-ārius||pos1="[[Janus]]"|pos2=adjectival suffix|nocat=1}}, with the first element perhaps from the [[Proto-Indo-European]] root {{m|ine-pro|*yeh₂-||to go}}. {{doublet|en|Gennaro}}.

