==Cebuano==

===Etymology===
From Proto-Central Philippine ''*may'' (existential marker).

===Pronunciation===
* {{ceb-IPA}}
* {{hyph|ceb|may}}

===Verb===
{{ceb-verb|b=+}}

# {{n-g|particle used as an existential marker}}: [[there be]]; [[there is]]
#: {{syn|ceb|anaa|aduna|adia|ania|atua}}
#: {{ant|ceb|wala}}
#: {{ux|ceb|'''may''' bulawan sa ungib|'''there is''' gold in the cave}}
#: {{ux|ceb|'''may''' dagkong mga pating sa dagat|the big sharks '''are''' in the sea}}
# {{n-g|particle used as a possessive marker}}: to [[have]]
#: {{ux|ceb|'''may''' sakyanan si Maria|Maria '''has''' a personal vehicle}}
# {{lb|ceb|after {{m|ceb|sa}}}} [[near]] a [[place]]
#: {{uxi|ceb|'''sa may''' pultahan|'''by''' the door}}
# {{lb|ceb|sometimes with [[mga]]}} [[approximately]], [[about]] [[some]] time ago; at [[around]]
#: {{uxi|ceb|'''may''' (mga) duha ka buwan na|it has been '''about''' two months}}
#: {{uxi|ceb|'''may''' (mga) alas-kuwatro|'''at around''' four o'clock}}
# {{lb|ceb|+ adjective prefixed with [[pagka-]]}} be [[somewhat]]
#: {{uxi|ceb|'''may pagka'''tabian si Antonio|Antonio is '''somewhat''' talkative}}

====Usage notes====
* In contrast to {{m|ceb|aduna}} and {{m|ceb|anaa}}, which behave as verbs and could thus take [[postpositive]] enclitics, [[may]] is a particle and is used immediately before the word modified.
*: {{uxi|ceb|'''may''' sakyanan siya|she '''has''' a car}}
*: {{uxi|ceb|'''may''' siya sakyanan|''is ungrammatical''}}

