#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Laura He|title=China woos Tesla, JP Morgan and other Western companies as foreign investment slumps|magazine=w:CNN Business|url=https://www.cnn.com/2023/09/19/economy/china-pboc-foreign-investment-drive-intl-hnk|date=2023-09-19|passage=Direct investment liabilities, a measure of FDI reflected in a country’s balance of payments, fell to just $4.9 billion in the April to '''June''' months, down 87% from a year earlier, according to data published by SAFE last month. That was the lowest amount in any quarter since records began in 1998.}}
