===Etymology===
{{etymon|la|septem<id:seven>|id=ninth month}}
By [[haplology]] from earlier {{m|la||*septemo-mēmbris|t=of or pertaining to the seventh month}}, from {{inh|la|itc-pro||*septemo-mēnzris}}, from {{m|la|septem|t=seven}} + {{m|la||*mēnsris}}, from {{affix|la|mensis|alt1=mens-|t1=month|-ris|nocat=1}}. In the {{w|Roman calendar}}, the year began with {{m|la|Mārtius|t=March}}, and {{m-self|la|September}} was the seventh month of the year.

