==Latin==

===Etymology===
{{etymon|la|octō<id:eight>|id=tenth month}}
By [[analogy]] with {{m|la|September}}, as if from {{m|la|octō}} and a suffix {{m|la|-ber}}. In the [[w:Roman calendar|Roman calendar]], the year began with {{m|la|Mārtius|t=March}}, and {{m|la||Octōber}} was the eighth month of the year.

===Pronunciation===
* {{la-IPA|Octōber}}

===Adjective===
{{la-adj|Octōber<3+>|noneut=1}}

# of {{l|en|October}}
#* '''1st century CE''' — [[w:Columella|Lucius Iunius Moderatus Columella]], ''[[s:la:De Re Rustica|De Re Rustica]]'', Book XII
#*: {{quote|la|Cum eius radicem mense '''Octobri''', quo[d] maxime matura est.}}
#* {{Q|la|Pope Francis|Est utique fiducia|year=2023|quote=Datum Romae, Laterani, die XV mensis '''Octobris''', in memoria sanctae Teresiae a Iesu, anno MMXXIII, Pontificatus Nostri undecimo}}

