==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{alt|en|Novembre||obsolete}}

===Etymology===
{{etymon|en|:inh|enm:Novembre<ety:bor<fro:novembre>>|tree=1}}
From {{inh|en|enm|Novembre}}, from {{der|en|fro|novembre}}, from {{der|en|la|November||ninth month}}, from Latin {{m|la|novem}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₁néwn̥||nine}}; + {{der|en|la|-ber}}, from {{m|la|-bris}}, an adjectival suffix. November was the ninth month in the Roman calendar.

Displaced native {{ncog|ang|blōtmōnaþ|lit=sacrifice month}}, so called because the {{w|Anglo-Saxons}}, when they were pagans, would sacrifice in this month before the winter set in.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/nəʊˈvɛmbə/|/nəˈvɛmbə/|a=UK}}
