==Latin==

===Etymology===
{{etymon|la|novem<id:nine>|id=eleventh month}}
By [[haplology]] from earlier {{m|la||*nove(m)-mēmbris|t=of or pertaining to the ninth month}}, from earlier {{m|la||*novem-mēnsris}}, from {{m|la|novem||nine}} + {{m|la||*mēnsris}}, from {{m|la|mensis|mens-|t=month}} + {{m|la|-ris}}. In the {{w|Roman calendar}}, the year began with {{m|la|Mārtius|t=March}}, and {{m|la||November}} was the ninth month of the year.

===Pronunciation===
* {{la-IPA}}

===Adjective===
{{la-adj|November<3+>|noneut=1}}

# of {{l|en|November}}
#* {{Q|la|Columella|De Re Rustica|6|quote='''Novembri''' mense ac Decembri per sementem quantum appetit bos.}}

