{{wp}}

===Etymology===
From {{af|en|multicultural|-ism}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˌmʌltɪˈkʌltʃəɹəˌlɪz(ə)m/|a=UK}}
* {{audio|en|en-au-multiculturalism.ogg|a=AU}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-multiculturalism.ogg|a=Mid-Atlantic US}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The characteristics of an organization, society, city etc. which has many different [[ethnic]] or [[national]] cultures mingling freely; political or social policies which support or encourage such [[coexistence]]. {{defdate|from 20th c.}}
#: {{cot|en|monoculturalism<qq:1>|biculturalism<qq:2>|triculturalism<qq:3>}}
#: {{nearsyn|en|polyculturalism<qq:several or many>}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1984|author=w:David Malouf|title=A First Place|page=18|publisher=Vintage|year_published=2015
|passage=The truth is that diversity, a kind of '''multiculturalism''' if we want to call it that, is the norm in any society.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=1991-04-08|author=Barbara Ehrenreich|magazine=Time|passage=Something had to replace the threat of communism, and at last a workable substitute is at hand. "'''Multiculturalism'''," as the new menace is known, has been denounced in the media recently as the new McCarthyism, the new fundamentalism, even the new totalitarianism – take your choice.|title=Essay: Teach Diversity – with a Smile}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2005-08-03|author=David Davis MP|work=Daily Telegraph|passage=Britain has pursued a policy of '''multiculturalism''' - allowing people of different cultures to settle without expecting them to integrate into society.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2011-04-07|title=On a mat and a prayer|magazine=The Economist|passage=Earlier this year he said '''multiculturalism''' had “failed”, that immigrants needed to “melt” into French society, and that “we do not want ostentatious prayers in the street in France.”}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Jennifer Hansler, Kylie Atwood and Nicole Gaouette|title=Pompeo attacks multiculturalism, saying it is ‘not who America is’|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/19/politics/pompeo-multiculturalism-tweet|date=2021-01-19|passage=Career diplomat Conrad Tribble said on Twitter that '''multiculturalism''' “is one of our greatest strengths as a country, and I go to that well often as an American diplomat. It’s hard to overstate the global soft power impact of America’s cultural diversity.”}}
# {{lb|en|derogatory|right-wing|colloquial}} The [[cultural Marxism]] conspiracy theory.

