===Noun===
{{head|enm|noun|altform=1}}

# {{tlb|enm|Late ME|Surrey}} {{alt form|enm|Tewesday}}

==English==
{{wp|<dab>}}

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*dʰegʷʰ-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|Wednesday}}, from unattested {{inh|en|ang|*wēdnesdæġ||Wednesday}}, synchronically an i-mutated form of attested {{m|ang|wōdnesdæġ}} (itself from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*Wōdanas dag}}, its reflex {{cog|enm|Wodnesdei}} falling into disuse), from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*Wōdinas dag}} also attested in {{cog|ofs|wednesdei}} and {{cog|dum|wenesdach}}. In any case, a calque ({{m|la|interpretātiō germānica}}) of {{der|en|la|diēs Mercuriī||day of Mercury}} and Koine {{cog|grc|ἡμέρα||day}} {{m|grc|Ἑρμοῦ||of Hermes}}, via an association of the god {{m|en|Odin||Woden}} with {{m|en|Mercury}} and {{m|en|Hermes}}. See also {{cog|ja|水曜日||Mercury's day}}.
{{col-top|2|cog}}
Cognate with {{cog|sco|Wadensday||Wednesday}}, {{cog|yol|Wennesdei||Wednesday}}, {{cog|fy|woansdei||Wednesday}}, {{cog|af|Woensdag||Wednesday}}, {{cog|gmw-cfr|Jodesdaach||Wednesday}}, {{cog|nl|-}}, {{cog|vls|woensdag||Wednesday}}, {{cog|nds-nl|woensdag}}, {{m|nds-nl|woonsdag}}, {{m|nds-nl|wonsdag||Wednesday}}, {{cog|de|Wodenstag}}, {{m|de|Wotanstag||Wednesday}}, {{cog|nds|Goonsdag}}, {{m|nds-de|Woonsdag||Wednesday}}, {{cog|da|-}}, {{cog|nb|-}}, {{cog|nn|-}}, {{cog|sv|onsdag||Wednesday}}, {{cog|fo|ónsdagur||Wednesday}}, {{cog|is|óðinsdagur||Wednesday}}.
{{col-bottom}}

