* {{IPA|en|/ˌkɒnəˈtæɪʃən/|a=NZ}}
* {{rhymes|en|eɪʃən|s=4}}
* {{hyphenation|en|con|no|ta|tion}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|semantics}} A [[meaning]] of a word or phrase that is [[suggest]]ed or [[implied]], as opposed to a [[denotation]], or [[literal]] [[meaning]]. A [[characteristic]] of [[word]]s or [[phrase]]s, or of the [[context]]s that words and phrases are used in.
#: {{ux|en|The word "advisedly" has a '''connotation''' of "wisely", although it denotes merely "intentionally" and "deliberately."}}
#: {{ux|en|The word "happy" has a positive '''connotation''', while "sad" has a negative '''connotation.'''}}
# {{lb|en|logic}} The [[attribute]] or aggregate of attributes [[connote]]d by a term, contrasted with {{m|en|denotation}}.
#: {{ux|en|The two expressions "the morning star" and "the evening star" have different '''connotations''' but the same denotation (i.e. the planet Venus).}}

