===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*(H)yeh₁-}}
From {{inh|en|enm|houre|houre}}, {{m|enm|hour}}, {{m|enm|oure}}, from {{der|en|fro|houre}}, from {{der|en|la|hōra||hour}}, from {{der|en|grc|ὥρα||any time or period, whether of the year, month, or day}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*yóh₁r̥||year, season}}. Akin to {{cog|ang|ġēar||year}}. {{doublet|en|hora|year}}. Compare ''[[horary]]''.

Partly displaced native {{cog|ang|tīd||time, hour}}, whence {{w|Modern English}} {{m|en|tide}}.

