# {{senseid|en|Q25235}}{{lb|en|time}} A unit of time of one twenty-fourth of a [[day]] (sixty [[minute]]s).
#: {{alti|en|mul:h<id:Q25235><qq:symbol>|hr<id:Q25235>|hrs<qq:alternative symbols>}}
#: {{syn|en|stound<qq:obsolete>}}
#: {{hol|en|day<id:Q573>|<|week<id:Q23387>|<|megasecond<id:Q1197459>|<|fortnight<id:Q2993680>|<|month<id:Q5151>|<|year<id:Q577>|<|gigasecond<id:Q1377051>|<|century<id:Q578>|<|kiloannum<id:Q3013059>|kiloyear<id:Q3013059>|millennium<id:Q36507>|<|terasecond<id:Q1322380>|<|mega-annum<id:Q20764>|megayear<id:Q20764>|<|petasecond<id:Q1066138>|<|giga-annum<id:Q524410>|gigayear<id:Q524410>|<|exasecond<id:Q906223>|<|zettasecond<id:Q12011178>|<|yottasecond<id:Q14913554>|<|ronnasecond<id:Q122972375>|<|quettasecond<id:Q116939356>}}
#: {{mer|en|quectosecond<id:Q125387265>|<|rontosecond<id:Q125387281>|<|yoctosecond<id:Q2762458>|<|zeptosecond<id:Q1872619>|<|attosecond<id:Q2483628>|<|femtosecond<id:Q1777507>|<|picosecond<id:Q3902709>|<|nanosecond<id:Q838801>|<|microsecond<id:Q842015>|<|millisecond<id:Q723733>|<|centisecond<id:Q3249364>|<|decisecond<id:Q3251645>|<|second<id:Q11574>|<|decasecond<id:Q1040401>|<|minute<id:Q7727>|<|hectosecond<id:Q1040427>|<|kilosecond<id:Q1374438>}}
#: {{nearsyn|en|microcentury<qq:humorous approximation>}}
#: {{ux|en|I spent an '''hour''' at lunch.}}
#: {{ux|en|There's a bus at 20 past the '''hour'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|We still have a couple '''hour'''s left to do in the yard.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1661|author={{w|John Fell (bishop)|John Fell}}|url=http://archive.org/stream/a615775104worduoft/a615775104worduoft_djvu.txt|title=The Life of the most learned, reverend and pious Dr. H. Hammond|passage=During the whole time of his abode in the university he generally spent thirteen '''hours''' of the day in study; by which assiduity besides an exact dispatch of the whole course of philosophy, he read over in a manner all classic authors that are extant{{...}}}}
#* {{RQ:Birmingham Gossamer|chapter=I|passage=It is never possible to settle down to the ordinary routine of life at sea until the screw begins to revolve. There is an '''hour''' or two, after the passengers have embarked, which is disquieting and fussy.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2014-06-21|volume=411|issue=8892|magazine=w:The Economist
|title=[http://www.economist.com/news/books-and-arts/21604535-real-sir-isaac-newton-was-not-first-king-reason-last Magician’s brain]
|passage=[Isaac Newton] was obsessed with alchemy. He spent '''hours''' copying alchemical recipes and trying to replicate them in his laboratory. He believed that the Bible contained numerological codes. The truth is that Newton was very much a product of his time.}}
# A [[season]], [[moment]], or [[time]].
#: {{ux|en|Don't come home ever again at this unearthly '''hour'''.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=c. 1829|author=w:Edgar Allan Poe|chapter=Alone|passage=From childhood's '''hour''' I have not been / As others were; I have not seen / As others saw; I could not bring / My passions from a common spring.|url=http://www.mdhs.org/digitalimage/poem-original-later-titled-alone|title=Archived copy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170405113118/http://www.mdhs.org/digitalimage/poem-original-later-titled-alone|archivedate=5 April 2017}}
#* {{RQ:Grey Riders|3|passage=Now will be a good '''hour''' to show you Milly Erne's grave.}}
# {{lb|en|poetic}} The [[time]].
#: {{ux|en|The '''hour''' grows late and I must go home.}}
# {{lb|en|military|in the plural}} Used after a two-digit hour and a two-digit minute to indicate time.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2000|author=T. C. G. James|title=The Battle of Britain|editor=Sebastian Cox|isbn=9780714651231|passage=By 1300 '''hours''' the position was fairly clear.}}
# {{lb|en|chiefly|in the plural}} The amount of labor demanded by an employer in terms of time.
#: {{ux|en|I asked my manager for more '''hours'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|The shop wasn't giving  me enough '''hours''' so I started searching for a second job.}}
# {{lb|en|Christianity|in the plural}} The set times of prayer, the [[canonical hour]]s, the offices or services prescribed for these, or a book containing them.
# {{lb|en|chiefly|_|US}} A distance that can be traveled in one hour.
#: {{ux|en|This place is an '''hour''' away from where I live.}}

