#: {{ux|en|Wait a '''minute''', I’m not ready yet!}}
# {{senseid|en|Q209426}}A unit of [[angle]] equal to one-sixtieth of a [[degree]].
#: {{syn|en|minute of arc|sexagesm|arcminute}}
#: {{ux|en|We need to be sure these maps are accurate to within one '''minute''' of arc.
}}
# {{lb|en|chiefly in the plural|[[minutes]]}} A (usually formal) written record of a meeting or a part of a meeting.
#: {{ux|en|Let’s look at the '''minutes''' of last week’s meeting.}}
#* {{quote-text|en|year=2008|author=Pink Dandelion|title=The Quakers: A Very Short Introduction|page=52
|passage=The Clerk or 'recording Clerk' drafts a '''minute''' and then, or at a later time, reads it to the Meeting. Subsequent contributions are on the wording of the '''minute''' only, until it can be accepted by the Meeting. Once the '''minute''' is accepted, the Meeting moves on to the next item on the agenda.}}
# A unit of purchase on a [[telephone]] or other similar [[network]], especially a [[cell phone]] network, roughly equivalent in [[gross]] form to sixty seconds' use of the network.
#: {{ux|en|If you buy this model, you’ll get 100 free '''minutes'''.}}
# A point in time; a moment.
#: {{syn|en|instant|moment|Thesaurus:point in time}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1675|author=w:John Dryden|title=w:Aureng-zebe|passage=Tell her, that I some Certainty may bring; / I go this '''minute''' to attend the king.}}
# A [[nautical]] or a [[geographic]] [[mile]].
# An old [[coin]], a [[half]] [[farthing]].
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A very small part of anything, or anything very small; a jot; a whit.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1660|author=Jeremy Taylor|title=Ductor Dubitantium, or, The Rule of Conscience in all her Generall Measures Serving as a Great Instrument for the Determination of Cases of Conscience|url=https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A63844.0001.001/1:9.1.4.2|volume=1|chapter=Of the Probable or Thinking Conscience.|passage={{...}}according to the Prophecies of him, which were so clear and descended to '''minutes''' and circumstances of his passion}}
# {{lb|en|architecture}} A fixed part of a [[module]].
# {{lb|en|slang|US|Canada|dialectal}} A [[while]] or a long unspecified period of time.
#: {{syn|en|age|spell|Thesaurus:eon}}
#: {{ux|en|Oh, I ain't heard that song in a '''minute'''!}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2010|author=Kenneth Ring|title=Letters from Palestine|pageurl=https://books.google.com/books?id=sLMRHc1aqSIC&lpg=PA18|page=18
|passage=“Man, I haven’t seen you in a '''minute''',” he says, smiling still. “Maybe like two, three years ago?”}}
#* {{quote-web|en|site=Complex.com|date=June 10 2010|url=https://www.complex.com/music/2010/06/lil-b-talks-getting-sucker-punched-gay-rumors-drake-envy|author=w:Lil B|passage=I seen {{w|Too$hort}} up there. Me and $hort ain't talked in a '''minute'''.}}
#* {{quote-av|en|date=2016-11-08|director=Ben Katai|writer=Ben Katai; Josh Corbin; Sharon Lennon|medium=TV|series=w:StartUp (TV series)|season=1|number=10|title=StartUp(Recapitalization)|actor=w:Edi Gathegi|role=Ronald Dacey|url=https://tvshowtranscripts.ourboard.org/viewtopic.php?f=705&t=28573|text=RON:I remember my first. I was a '''minute''' younger than you. {{...}}I remember thinking, saying to myself..."This is the first time I'm eating as a person who killed someone."}}

