===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|trade|t=path, course of conduct}}, introduced into English by Hanseatic merchants, from {{der|en|gml|trade|t=track, course}}, from {{der|en|osx|trada|t=spoor, track}}, from {{der|en|gmw-pro|*tradu}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*tradō|t=track, way}}, and cognate with {{cog|ang|tredan|t=to tread}}; ultimately from {{der|en|ine-pro|*dreh₂-|t=to tread, walk, step, run}}. 

Cognate with {{cog|nl|trade}}, {{m|nl|tra|t=path, trail, course, trade}}, {{cog|nds-de|Traad|t=track, wagon trail}}, {{cog|lb|Tratt|t=step, pace}}, {{cog|is|tröð|t=a lane between fences, enclosure, pen}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/tɹeɪd/|a=RP,GA}}
* {{audio|en|En-uk-trade.ogg|a=RP}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Naomi Persephone Amethyst (NaomiAmethyst)-trade.wav|a=GA}}
* {{audio|en|En-us-trade.ogg|a=GA}}
* {{rhymes|en|eɪd|s=1}}
* {{homophones|en|trayed}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[buying]] and [[selling]] of [[goods]] and [[services]] on a [[market]].
#: {{syn|en|commerce}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} A particular instance of [[buy]]ing or [[sell]]ing, or a series of related transactions executed as a single investment.
#: {{syn|en|deal|barter}}
#: {{ux|en|I did no '''trades''' with them once the rumors started.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} An idea or strategy for an investment on a market.
#: {{ux|en|"Sell America" is the latest '''trade''' on Wall Street.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} An instance of [[barter]]ing items in [[exchange]] for one another.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1989|author=w:Bruce Pandolfini|title=Chess Openings: Traps and Zaps|isbn=0671656902|section=Glossary|page=225|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=pocVITTr8tMC&pg=PA225&dq=trade|passage=EXCHANGE — A '''trade''' or swap of no material profit to either side.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2009|author=Elliott Kalb; Mark Weinstein|title=The 30 Greatest Sports Conspiracy Theories of All Time|isbn=9781602396784|page=60|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=nQd8MHuaXysC&pg=PA60&dq=trade|passage=When Golden State matched the Knicks' offer sheet, the Warriors and Knicks worked out a '''trade''' that sent King to New York for Richardson.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} Those who [[perform]] a particular kind of [[skilled]] work.
#: {{syn|en|business}}
#: {{ux|en|The skilled '''trades''' were the first to organize modern labor unions.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=w:Edwin Black| title=Internal Combustion| chapter=2| url=http://openlibrary.org/works/OL4103950W| passage=But through the oligopoly, charcoal fuel proliferated throughout London's '''trades''' and industries.&nbsp; By the 1200s, brewers and bakers, tilemakers, glassblowers, pottery producers, and a range of other craftsmen all became hour-to-hour consumers of charcoal.}}
# {{lb|en|countable}} Those engaged in an industry or group of related industries.
#: {{ux|en|It is not a retail showroom. It is only for the '''trade'''.}}
# {{senseid|en|skilled practice of a practical occupation}} {{lb|en|countable}} The skilled practice of a practical [[occupation]].
#: {{syn|en|craft}}
#: {{ux|en|He learned his '''trade''' as an [[apprentice]].}}
#* '''1969''', Paul Simon, Simon & Garfunkel, “The Boxer”, ''Bridge over Troubled Water'', Columbia Records:
#*: In the clearing stands a boxer and a fighter by his '''trade'''
# {{lb|en|countable|or|uncountable}} An [[occupation]] in the [[secondary sector]], as opposed to an [[agricultural]], [[professional]] or [[military]] one.
#: {{ux|en|After failing his entrance exams, he decided to go into a '''trade'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|Most veterans went into '''trade''' when the war ended.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2007|author=Michael Lynch| title=The Oxford Companion to Scottish History| publisher=Oxford University Press| location=USA| isbn=9780199234820| page=228| passage=Subsequently some Scottish troops settled, took up '''trade''' as weavers, tailors, or mariners, and married Dutch women.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2012|author=Liberty Carrington|title=Wide Eyes Closed|publisher=AuthorHouse|isbn=9781477293898|page=92|passage=Getting a job in your major is no breeze: Remember we made fun of those who took up a '''trade'''}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable|UK}} The [[business]] given to a [[commercial]] [[establishment]] by its customers.
#: {{syn|en|business|takings|custom|footfall|patronage}}
#: {{ux|en|Even before noon there was considerable '''trade'''.}}
#: {{ux|en|'''Trade''' has been down in this cold weather.}}
#: {{ux|en|The gift shop relies on passing '''trade''' from tourists.}}
# {{lb|en|mostly|in the plural}} [[steady|Steady]] [[wind]]s blowing from east to west above and below the [[equator]].
#: {{ux|en|They rode the '''trades''' going west.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1826|author=James Horsburgh|title=India Directory, Or Directions for Sailing to and from the East Indies, China, New Holland, Cape of Good Hope, Brazil and the Interjacent Ports|page=28|text=Calms and variable winds, are also experienced during every month of the year, in the space between the '''trades''';{{...}} the vicinity of the north-east '''trade''' seems most liable to them.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ctJYAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA28|origyear=1816}}
# {{lb|en|only as plural}} A publication intended for participants in an industry or related group of industries.
#: {{ux|en|Rumors about layoffs are all over the '''trades'''.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable|gay slang}} A [[masculine]] man available for [[casual sex]] with men, often for pay. {{non-gloss|(Compare ''[[rough trade]]''.)}}
#: {{ux|en|Josh picked up some '''trade''' last night.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|year=1950|author=w:W. H. Auden|title=A Playboy of the Western World: St. Oscar, The Homintern Martyr|journal=w:Partisan Review|url=http://archives.bu.edu/collections/partisan-review/search/detail?id=284002|page=391–2|text=In a homosexual of this kind—corresponding to the test of eccentric behavior in the drawing-room—one usually finds a preference for "'''trade'''," i.e., sexually normal males, because, if another homosexual yields to him, he is only one of a class, but if he can believe that an exception is being made in his case, it seems a proof that he is being accepted for himself alone.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete|uncountable}} Instruments of any occupation.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1697|author=w:John Dryden|title=The works of Virgil containing his Pastorals, Georgics and Aeneis|page=112|text=His House and household Gods! his '''trade''' of War, / His Bow and Quiver; and his trusty Cur.|chapter=The Third Book of the Georgics|url=https://quod.lib.umich.edu/e/eebo/A65112.0001.001/1:18.3?rgn=div2;view=fulltext}}
# {{short for|en|trade paperback}}
# {{lb|en|mining}} Refuse or rubbish from a mine.
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A track or trail; a way; a path; [[passage]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1557|author=w:Henry Howard, Earl of Surrey|title=The Second Book of Virgil's Æneid| passage=A postern with a blind wicket there was, / A common '''trade''' to pass through Priam's house}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1590|author=w:Edmund Spenser|title=w:The Faerie Queene|section=Book II|passage=As Shepheardes curre, that in darke eveninges shade / Hath tracted forth some salvage beastes '''trade'''}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=c. 1595|author=w:William Shakespeare|title=Richard II|section=act III, scene iii|passage=Or, I'll be buried in the king's highway, / Some way of common '''trade''', where subjects' feet / May hourly trample on their sovereign's head.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A course; a custom; a practice; an occupation.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1545|author=w:Nicholas Udall|title=Paraphrase on Luke|by=w:Desiderius Erasmus|passage=The Jewes, emong whom alone and no moe, God hitherto semed for to reigne, by reason of their knowledge of the law, and of the autoritee of being in the right '''trade''' of religion.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1590|author=w:Edmund Spenser|title=w:The Faerie Queene|section=Book II|passage=There those five sisters had continual '''trade''' / And used to bathe themselves in that deceitful shade.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1655|author=w:Philip Massinger; {{w|John Fletcher (playwright)|John Fletcher}}|title=w:A Very Woman|passage=Long did I love this lady, / Long was my travel, long my '''trade''' to win her.}}
