{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To [[engage]] in [[#Noun|trade]].
#: {{syn|en|deal}}
#: {{ux|en|This company '''trades''' (in) precious metal.}}
#: {{ux|en|He withdrew money to his bank account after several years of '''trading''' stocks on E-Trade.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1727|author=John Arbuthnot|title=Tables of Ancient Coins, Weights and Measures|page=248|text={{...}}a free port, where Nations warring with one another resorted with their Goods, and '''traded''' as in a neutral Country.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UmBMAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA248}}
# {{lb|en|finance|intransitive|copulative}} To be traded at a certain price or under certain conditions.
#: {{ux|en|Apple is '''trading''' at $200.}}
#: {{ux|en|ExxonMobil '''trades''' on the NYSE.}}
#: {{ux|en|The stock is '''trading''' rich relative to its sector.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|with '''for'''}} To give (something) in [[exchange]] (for).
#: {{syn|en|exchange|swap|switch|truck|id4=trade}}
#: {{ux|en|Will you '''trade''' your precious watch for my earring?}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[mutually]] [[exchange]] (something) (with).
#: {{ux|en|The rival schoolboys '''traded''' insults and punches.}}
#* {{quote-video game|en|developer=Bungie|authorlink=Bungie|title=w:Halo 3|publisher=w:Microsoft Game Studios|date=25 September 2007|system=w:Xbox 360|level=[https://www.halopedia.org/Terminal_(Halo_3)#The_terminals Terminal Six (Legendary)]|passage=The [Halo effect] strikes our combined fleets. All ships piloted by biologicals are now [adrift]. I can '''trade''' Mendicant ship for ship now and still prevail.}}
#* {{quote-av|en|author=Drachinifel|title=The Battle of Samar - Odds? What are those?|date=27 February 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4AdcvDiA3lE|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20221103043318/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4AdcvDiA3lE|archivedate=3 November 2022|accessdate=5 November 2022|time=29:08|text=''Kalinin Bay'' is also in trouble, '''trading''' fire with Japanese destroyers and taking hits from both them and cruisers at the same time.  Unlike the ''Gambier Bay'', however, it does not appear that ''these'' ships have realized they need to switch to high explosive from armor-piercing, and, despite being riddled with shellfire, the ship stays afloat, despite this rather-unequal battering going on for another twenty to thirty minutes.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|with '''on'''}} To use or exploit a particular aspect, such as a name, reputation, or image, to gain advantage or benefit.
#: {{syn|en|exploit|[[capitalize]] on|[[take advantage]] of|use|leverage|[[benefit]] from|[[make use]] of|milk}}
#: {{ux|en|Some musicians try to '''trade on''' their past success by playing the same hits over and over again.}}
# {{lb|en|gardening|transitive|or|intransitive}} To [[give]] someone a [[plant]] and [[receive]] a [[different]] one in [[return]].
# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To do business; offer for sale as for one's [[livelihood]].
#: {{syn|en|do business}}
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To have dealings; to be concerned or associated (with).
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Macbeth|III|v|passage=Saucy and over bold, how did you dare / To '''trade''' and traffic with Macbeth}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[recommend]] and get [[recommendation]]s.
#: {{syn|en|exchange}}

