====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{senseid|en|Q24905}}{{lb|en|grammar}} A [[word]] that indicates an action, event, or state of being.
#: {{ux|en|The word “speak” is an English '''verb'''.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|url=https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k45595/f201.item|date=18 July 1530|author=[[w:John Palsgrave|Iohan Palſgrave]]|title=Leſclarciſſement de la langue francoyſe{{...}}|publisher=Richard Pynſon, Iohan Haukyns|location=London|oclc=715474564|newversion=reprinted as|year2=1972|publisher2=Slatkine Reprints|location2=Genève|title2=Lesclarcissement de la langue françoyse|chapter=The Introduction|page=32|passage=In ſo moche that if any '''verbe''' be of the thyꝛde coniugation / I ſet out all his rotes and tenſes{{...}}}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} Any [[word]]; a [[vocable]].
#* {{RQ:South Twelve Sermons|passage=a '''Verb''' of the Singular}}
# {{lb|en|figurative}} An action as opposed to a trait or thing.
#: {{ux|en|Kindness is a '''verb''', not an adjective. You're only kind if you do kind things.}}
# {{lb|en|programming}} A named command that performs a specific [[operation]] on an [[object]].
#* {{quote-text|en|year=1995|author=Adam Denning|title=OLE Controls Inside Out|page=321
|passage=You can invoke the Properties OLE '''verb''' in many ways. The easiest way is to move the mouse over the border of the control until it becomes only a four-way pointer and then right-click.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=2016|author=Ada Gavrilovska|title=Attaining High Performance Communications: A Vertical Approach|passage=The InfiniBand '''verbs''', which are closely modeled in the “Gen2” interface, provide the functional specification for the operations that should be allowed on an InfiniBand compliant adapter.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* Verbs compose a fundamental category of words in most languages. In an English clause, a verb forms the [[head]] of the [[predicate]] of the clause. In many languages, verbs uniquely [[conjugate]] for [[tense]] and [[aspect]].

=====Quotations=====
* {{quote-text|en|year=2001|author=w:Eoin Colfer|title=Artemis Fowl|page=221
|passage=Then you could say that the doorway exploded. But the particular '''verb''' doesn't do the action justice. Rather, it shattered into infinitesimal pieces.}}

