From {{inh|en|enm|adjectif}}, {{m|enm|adjective}}, from {{der|en|fro|adjectif}}, from {{der|en|la|adiectivus}}, from {{m|la|adiciō}} + {{m|la|-īvus}}, from {{m|la|ad-||to, towards, at}} + {{m|la|iaciō||throw}}. The Latin word {{m|la|adiectivus}} in turn was a calque of {{noncog|grc|ἐπιθετικόν|t=added}}, a derivative of the compound verb {{m|grc|ἐπιτίθημι}}, from which also comes {{m|en|epithet}}.

