# {{senseid|en|Q34698}} {{lb|en|grammar}} A [[word]] that [[modify|modifies]] a [[noun]]  or noun phrase or [[describe]]s a noun’s referent.
#: {{ux|en|The words “big” and “heavy” are English '''adjectives'''.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1932|year_published=1965|author=w:Delos W. Lovelace|title=[[w:King Kong (1933 film)|King Kong]]|page=8|passage="They'll have to invent new '''adjectives''' when I come back. You wait!"}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Jessie Yeung|title=Pope Francis loves nouns but is ‘allergic’ to adjectives|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2011/sep/01/sport-language-harry-pearson|date=2019-09-24|passage="We have fallen into the culture of '''adjectives''' and adverbs, and we have forgotten the strength of nouns," he said.|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927032029/https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/24/us/pope-adjectives-intl-hnk-scli/|quotee=w:Pope Francis}}
