===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# {{lb|en|grammar}} [[adjectival|Adjectival]]; pertaining to or functioning as an adjective.
#: {{syn|en|adjectival}}
# {{lb|en|legal}} Applying to methods of enforcement and rules of procedure.
#* {{RQ:Macaulay History of England|chapter=10|passage=The whole English law, substantive and '''adjective'''.}}
#: {{syn|en|procedural}}
#: {{ant|en|substantive}}
# {{lb|en|chemistry|of a [[dye]]}} Needing the use of a [[mordant]] to be made [[fast]] to that which is being dyed.
#: {{ant|en|substantive}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete|reflected in the chemical sense, but extinct as a general sense}} Incapable of independent function.
#* '''1899''', [[w:John Jay Chapman|John Jay Chapman]], ''Emerson and Other Essays'', AMS Press (1969) (as [http://www.gutenberg.org/etext/13088 reproduced] in Project Gutenberg)
#*: In fact, God is of not so much importance in Himself, but as the end towards which man tends. That irreverent person who said that Browning uses “God” as a pigment made an accurate criticism of his theology. In Browning, God is '''adjective''' to man.
#: {{syn|en|dependent|derivative}}
#: {{cot|en|adjunct|adjunctive|adjutant}}

