# Of the [[essence]] or essential [[element]] of a thing.
#: {{syn|en|essential|in essence}}
#: {{ux|en|'''substantive''' information}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=6 October 2012|magazine=w:The Economist|url=http://www.economist.com/node/21564222|title=The first presidential debate: Back in the centre, back in the game|passage=In one sense the first debate achieved the worst of all worlds: it managed to be technical, even dull, without being '''substantive''' or especially honest.|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/GdKyR|archivedate=2023-03-08}}
## {{lb|en|by extension}} Constituting the substance of {{l|en|content|id=semantic information}} rather than its style, and thus always [[nontrivial]].
##: {{ux|en|'''Substantive''' editing is never trivial, whereas some aspects of copyediting are trivial.}}
##: {{ux|en|'''substantive''' changes made by the lawyers}}
# {{senseid|en|substantial}} Having [[substance]]; enduring; [[solid]]; firm; [[substantial]].
#: {{syn|en|meaty|substantial}}
#: {{ant|en|superficial|trivial}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1836|origyear=1829|title=Literary Remains of the Late William Hazlitt|chapter=Definition of wit|page=19|author=w:William Hazlitt|passage=Once more then, strength and magnitude are qualities which impress the imagination in a powerful and '''substantive''' manner;|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wTbQAAAAMAAJ&pg=PA19}}
# {{senseid|en|legal rights}}{{lb|en|law}} Applying to essential [[legal]] [[principle]]s and [[rule]]s of right.
#: {{ant|en|adjective|procedural}}
#: {{ux|en|'''substantive''' law}}
#* {{RQ:NYT|title=Amy Coney Barrett Is Looking Beyond the Trump Era|date=2025-10-16|author=w:Ross Douthat|quotee=w:Amy Coney Barrett|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/16/opinion/amy-coney-barrett-interesting-times-podcast.html|passage=So this test, this whole area of '''substantive''' due process, is tricky for some of the reasons you say. That’s been a criticism of the doctrine in general and a criticism of the general notion that we can have rights that the Constitution doesn’t specify, precisely because of the kind of inquiry that it invites judges to undertake.|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/rQdBa|archivedate=2025-10-20}}
# {{lb|en|chemistry|of a dye}} Not needing the use of a [[mordant]] to be made [[fast]] to that which is being dyed.
#: {{ant|en|adjective}}
# Depending on itself; [[independent]].
#* {{RQ:Bacon New Atlantis|page=16|passage=Hee therefore taking into Conſideration, how ſufficient and '''ſuſstantiue''' this Land was, to maintaine it ſelfe without any aid (at all) of the foreigner; {{...}}}}
# {{lb|en|grammar}} Of or pertaining to a {{l|en|substantive|id=noun}}.
#: {{syn|en|substantival}}
# {{lb|en|military|of a rank or appointment}} {{cap|actually}} and [[legally]] held, as distinct from an [[acting]], [[temporary]] or [[honorary]] [[rank]] or [[appointment]].

