====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|archaic|_|in general sense}} An act of dealing or sharing out.
# {{lb|en|card games}} The distribution of cards to players; a player's turn for this.
#: {{syn|en|hand}}
#: {{ux|en|I didn’t have a good '''deal''' all evening.}}
#: {{ux|en|I believe it's your '''deal'''.}}
# {{senseid|en|transaction}} A particular instance of [[trading#Noun|trading]] (buying or selling; exchanging; bartering); a [[transaction]].
#: {{syn|en|business deal|sale|trade|transaction}}
#: {{ux|en|We need to finalise the '''deal''' with Henderson by midnight.}}
#: {{ux|en|recognizing the societal '''deal''' between capital and labor regarding retirement savings}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Jamie Jackson|title=Ángel di María says Manchester United were the ‘only club’ after Real|titleurl=http://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/aug/26/angel-di-maria-completes-move-to-manchester-united|journal=The Guardian|date=26 August 2014
|passage=The '''deal''', which overtakes the £50m paid to Liverpool by Chelsea for Fernando Torres in January 2011 as the highest paid by a British club, takes United’s summer spend to £130.7m, following the £27m spent on Luke Shaw, the £28m for Ander Herrera and £16m for Marcos Rojo.}}
# {{senseid|en|good bargain}} {{lb|en|in particular}} A [[transaction]] offered which is financially beneficial; a [[bargain]].
#: {{syn|en|steal|bargain}}
#* '''2009''', ''The Guardian'', Virginia Wallis, 22 Jul 2009:
#*: You also have to look at the kind of mortgage '''deals''' available to you and whether you will be able to trade up to the kind of property you are looking for.
# {{senseid|en|arrangement}} An [[agreement]] between parties; an [[arrangement]].
#: {{syn|en|contract|pact}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Jennifer Steinhauer|journal=New York Times|date=20 Jul 2009
|passage=California lawmakers, their state broke and its credit rating shot, finally sealed the '''deal''' with the governor Monday night on a plan to close a $26 billion budget gap.}}
#: {{uxi|en|He made a '''deal''' with the devil.}}
#: {{uxi|en|I didn't deserve it, but he cut me a '''deal'''.}}
#: {{coi|en|to cut a '''deal''', to cut '''deals'''}}
#: {{coi|en|to cut a fantastic '''deal''', to cut a raw '''deal'''}}
# {{senseid|en|situation}} {{lb|en|informal}} A [[situation]], [[occasion]], or [[event]].
#: {{ux|en|What's the '''deal''' here?}}
#: {{ux|en|Their new movie is the biggest '''deal''' of the year.}}
#: {{ux|en|I don't think that's such a [[big deal|big '''deal''']].}}
# {{lb|en|informal}} A [[thing]], an unspecified or unidentified [[object]].
#: {{syn|en|dealy|thingy|whazzit}}
#: {{ux|en|The '''deal''' with four tines is called a pitchfork.}}
#* {{quote-av|en|title=w:Broken Arrow|year=1996|author=w:Graham Yost|passage=I've never killed anybody before. I don't see what's the big '''deal'''.|role=Major Vic "Deak" Deakins|actor=John Travolta}}
# {{lb|en|slang|of a person}} A personality trait, especially a negative one, and the underlying cause of it.
#: {{ux|en|What's her '''deal'''?}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1990|author=National Archives and Records Administration|quotee=Bill Clinton|title=George Bush: 1992-1993|page=1861
|text=His whole '''deal''' is, you've got to be for it or against it, and you can't make it better.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2006-02-06|title=Dr. Boy|journal=ELLEgirl
|text=My boyfriend hates it when I wear makeup or put on a short skirt, but then he points out how hot girls like the Pussycat Dolls are. What's his '''deal'''? —Jill, 16, Fresno, CA}}
#* {{quote-book|en|date=2017-04-11|author=Amber Portwood|title=Never Too Late|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=9781682613276|page=90
|text=I don't know what her '''deal''' was. I think she just cared about the MTV stuff and wanted to be around us, maybe hoping a camera would show up and she'd get her face on the color TV or something.}}

