===Etymology 1===
{{etymon|en|id=Q23640|:inh|enm:heed<id:head>|tree=1}}
From {{inh|en|enm|hed}} {{m|enm|heed}}, from {{inh|en|ang|hēafod|hēafd-, hēafod|head, top, chief}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*haubud}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*haubudą||head}}, from {{inh|en|ine-pro|*káput}}. 

The modern word comes from Old English oblique stem ''hēafd-''; the expected Modern English outcome for ''hēafod'' would be ''*heaved'' (similar to the Middle English word). {{doublet|en|cape|capo|caput|chef|chief|Howth}}.

Cognate with {{cog|ang|hafela||head}}, {{cog|sco|heid}}, {{m|sco|hede}}, {{m|sco|hevid}}, {{m|sco|heved||head}}, {{cog|frr|hood||head}}, {{cog|nl|hoofd||head}}, {{cog|de|Haupt||head}}, {{cog|da|hoved||head}}, {{cog|fo|høvd}}, {{m|fo|høvur||head}}, {{cog|is|höfuð||head}}, {{cog|nrn|heved||head}}, {{cog|no|hode||head}}, {{m|no|hoved-||head, chief, main, principal}}, {{cog|sv|huvud||head}}, {{cog|la|caput||head}}, {{cog|hi|कपाल||skull}}, {{cog|sa|कपाल||skull}}.

