===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{senseid|en|Q165308}}A [[domesticated]] [[plant]], in species {{taxfmt|Cucurbita pepo|species}}, similar in [[growth]] pattern, [[foliage]], [[flower]], and [[fruit]] to the [[squash]] or [[melon]].
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Batchimeg Togoobat, Nan Wu, Xifeng Wang, Mengji Cao, Zhongtian Xu|title=Viromic approach reveals differences in the composition, diversity and relative abundance of pumpkin viruses across main growing regions of China|journal=Virology|volume=585|doi=10.1016/j.virol.2023.05.005|page=61-71|date=2023-08|passage=Nevertheless, the comprehensive comparative analysis of '''pumpkin''' viromes across various geographic regions by NGS remains deficient.}}
# The [[round]] [[yellow]] or [[orange]] fruit of this plant.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1904|author=w:L. Frank Baum|title=The Marvelous Land of Oz|url=http://www.literature.org/authors/baum-l-frank/the-marvelous-land-of-oz/chapter-01.html|passage=There were '''pumpkins''' in Mombi’s corn-fields, lying golden red among the rows of green stalks; and these had been planted and carefully tended that the four-horned cow might eat of them in the winter time.}}
# {{lb|en|uncountable}} The typical [[color]] of the ripe fruit of the pumpkin plant.
#: {{color panel|FF7518}}
# {{lb|en|Australia}} Any of a number of [[cultivar]]s from the genus {{taxfmt|Cucurbita|genus}}; ''known in the US as [[winter squash]]''.
# {{lb|en|US}} {{non-gloss|A [[term of endearment]] for someone [[small]] and [[cute]].}}
#* {{quote-song|en|year=1991|author=w:John Prine; Pat McLaughlin|title=Daddy’s Little '''Pumpkin'''|album=w:The Missing Years (album)|passage=You must be daddy’s little '''pumpkin'''.}}
# {{lb|en|informal|automotive}} The [[housing#Noun|housing]] for a [[differential#Noun|differential]], built into an [[axle#Noun|axle]] of a vehicle; the housing and its contents.

