==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|la|Fabiānus||belonging to Fabius}}, derived from {{m|la|Fabius}} + {{m|la|-ānus}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|fā'''′'''bē-ən}}
* {{IPA|en|/ˈfeɪ.biː.ən/|a=RP}}
* {{IPA|en|/ˈfeɪ.bi.ən/|a=GenAm,CanE}}
* {{IPA|en|/ˈfæɪ.biː.ən/|a=AuE,NZE}}
* {{IPA|en|/ˈfe.bi.ən/|a=ScE}}
* {{IPA|en|/ˈfeː.biː.an/|a=InE}}
* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Vealhurl-Fabian.wav|a=Southern England}}
* {{rhymes|en|eɪbiən|s=3}}
* {{hyph|en|Fa|bi|an}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{lb|en|military}} Pertaining to or reminiscent of Roman general {{w|Fabius Maximus}}, whose tactics against Hannibal during the Second Punic War famously consisted of delaying or avoiding combat, focusing instead on weakening the enemy by cutting off supply lines.
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1988|author=James McPherson|title=Battle Cry of Freedom|publisher=Oxford|year_published=2004|page=745|passage=Hood complained behind his commander's back to Richmond of Johnston's '''Fabian''' strategy.}}
#* {{quote-av|en|author=Tina Fey|authorlink=Tina Fey|actor={{w|Alec Baldwin}}|role={{w|Jack Donaghy}}|episode={{w|The Fabian Strategy}}|title={{w|30 Rock}}|url=https://www.peacocktv.com/watch-online/tv/30-rock/6240863759978157112/seasons/5/episodes/the-fabian-strategy-episode-1/89f86a3e-9cbd-34d0-880c-c5fe00a9769a|season={{w|30 Rock season 5|5}}|number=1|date=September 23, 2010|time=5:03|text=“This is how I know you've never had an adult relationship. If I say no, then I will be required to say yes to something else in the future, and the stakes in the future might be higher.” “Then say yes.” “If I give in, then I'm no longer the alpha in my house. Before you know it, she'll have me wearing jeans and reading fiction!” “Yeah, well, yes and no are kind of your only two choices.” “For most men, sure. But there is a third option. The '''Fabian''' strategy.” “I know this. If an apple and a feather fall at the same time--” “The '''Fabian''' strategy derives its name from the Roman general Quintus Fabius Maximus. He ran away, Lemon. Rather than engage in battle, he would retreat and retreat until the enemy grew fatigued and eventually made a mistake. Although I abhor it as a military strategy, it is the basis for all of my, uh, personal relationships.” “So Avery is your enemy. That sounds healthy.” “You're in no position to judge.”}}
# {{lb|en|political}} Advocating that social reforms be reached through a series of gradual and moderate stages rather than sudden [[revolution]]; specifically, relating to the Fabian Society, a British socialist society advocating [[reformist]] [[socialism]].
# {{lb|en|by extension}} [[cautious|Cautious]]; [[dilatory]]; [[avoiding]] a [[decisive]] contest.

