==Tagalog==

===Etymology 1===
{{bor+|tl|es|a}}, from {{der|tl|la|ad}}.

====Pronunciation====
{{tl-pr}}

====Prefix====
{{tl-head|prefix|b=+}}

# [[at]] {{gl|indicating time}}
#: {{ux|tl|Puntahan kita sa '''a-primero''' ng Marso.|I'll go to you at the '''first''' of March.}}
#: {{ux|tl|Sahuran tuwing '''a-kinse''' ng bawat buwan.|It is payday every '''15{{sup|th}} '''of every month.}}
#: {{ux|tl|'''A-treynta y uno''' kahapon.|Yesterday was the '''31{{sup|st}}'''.}}

=====Usage notes=====
* Only used before Spanish cardinal numbers to tell the date for a month. For the first day of a month, {{m|tl|a-primero}} is more correct but {{m|tl|a-uno}} is also used by younger speakers. The prefix has the same function as {{m|tl|ika-}} for Tagalog cardinal numbers.
* The prefix is optional but Spanish-oriented speakers often use it.

=====Derived terms=====
{{prefixsee|tl}}

===Etymology 2===

====Pronunciation====
{{tl-pr|áː-}}

====Prefix====
{{tl-head|prefix|á-|b=+}} {{tlb|tl|dialectal|chiefly|Mindoro}}

# {{n-g|forms contemplative aspect forms for verbs in the object or directional trigger}}

=====Usage notes=====
* Can be considered as a dialectal equivalent to the reduplicated syllable for some verbs.
*: {{afex|tl|á-|tápon<t:throw>|átápon<t:will be thrown>}}: equivalent to {{m|tl|itatapon}}
*: {{afex|tl|á-|inóm<t:drink>|-in|áinumín<t:will be drunk>}}: equivalent to {{m|tl|iinumin}}
*: {{afex|tl|á-|gawâ<t:drink>|-an|ágaw-án<t:will be done for>}}: equivalent to {{m|tl|gagawan}}
*: {{afex|tl|á-|pakuluan<t:to be boiled>|ápakuluán<t:will let to be boiled>}}: equivalent to {{m|tl|pakukuluan}}
* When used with {{m|tl|in-}}, forms the progressive aspect forms of verbs.
*: {{afex|tl|in-|á-|tápon<t:throw>|inátápon<t:being thrown>}}: equivalent to {{m|tl|itinatapon}}
*: {{afex|tl|in-|á-|inóm<t:drink>|ináinóm<t:being drunk>}}: equivalent to {{m|tl|iniinom}}
*: {{afex|tl|in-|á-|gawâ<t:drink>|-an|inágaw-án<t:being done for>}}: equivalent to {{m|tl|ginagawan}}
*: {{afex|tl|in-|á-|pakuluan<t:to be let boiled>|inápakuluán<t:letting to be boiled>}}: equivalent to {{m|tl|pinakukuluan}}

