#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=A YOLA ZONG|number=14|page=90|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=Jaane got leigheen; shoo pleast '''aam''' all, fowe?|translation=Joan set them a laughing, she pleased '''them''' all, how?}}
#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=A YOLA ZONG|number=14|page=90|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|passage=Shoo ya '''aam''' zim to doone, as w' be doone nowe;|translation=She gave '''them''' some to do, as we are doing now;}}
#* {{quote-book|yol|year=1867|chapter=VERSES IN ANSWER TO THE WEDDEEN O BALLYMORE|number=2|title=SONGS, ETC. IN THE DIALECT OF FORTH AND BARGY|page=100|passage=Craneen t' thee wee '''aam''', thee luggès shell aake.|translation=Choking to thee with '''them'''. Thy ears shall ache.}}

